GitHub plugin for Claude Code
=============================

This product includes software developed by OpenAI and contributors to the
`openai/plugins` repository (https://github.com/openai/plugins).

Portions of this plugin — specifically the skills under `skills/` and the
helper scripts under `skills/*/scripts/` — were adapted from OpenAI's
`github@openai-curated` plugin for Codex, which is licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0.

Modifications from the original:

- Removed references to OpenAI's proprietary Apps & Connectors registry
  (the `.app.json` file and any "GitHub app from this plugin" / "connector"
  language in skill instructions).
- Rewrote every "use the GitHub app from this plugin" instruction to use
  the `gh` CLI via Claude Code's Bash tool, since Claude Code has no
  connector-registry analog today.
- Dropped Codex-specific runtime metadata (`agents/openai.yaml` files) that
  do not apply to Claude Code.
- Moved plugin metadata from `.codex-plugin/plugin.json` to
  `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` and updated fields for Claude Code's plugin
  format.

The Python helper scripts under `skills/gh-fix-ci/scripts/` and
`skills/gh-address-comments/scripts/` are included unchanged and carry the
same Apache License 2.0 terms.

A full copy of the Apache License 2.0 is included as the LICENSE file at
the root of this plugin directory.
